obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (23475)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00003_200502_1517807320310&sectionId=23475&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00003_200502_1517807320310
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the National Commission`
  line `for Minority Educational Institutions Act, 2004.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India ^1***.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall be deemed to have come into force on the 11th day of November, 2004.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "except the State of Jammu and Kashmir" omitted by Act 34 of 2019, s. 95 and the Fifth Schedule (w.e.f. 31-10-`
  line `2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (23476)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00003_200502_1517807320310&sectionId=23476&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00003_200502_1517807320310
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "affiliation" together with its grammatical variations, includes, in relation to a college,`
  line `recognition of such college by, association of such college with, and admission of such college to the`
  line `privileges of, a ^1`
  line `*** University;`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[(aa) appropriate Government means,--`
  line
  line `(i) in relation to an educational institution recognised for conducting its programmes of`
  line `studies under any Act of Parliament, the Central Government; and`
  line
  line `(ii) in relation to any other educational institution recognised for conducting its programmes`
  line `of studies under any State Act, a State Government in whose jurisdiction such institution is`
  line established;]
  line
  line ^3
  line `* * * * *`
  line
  line `(c) "Commission" means the National Commission for Minority Educational Institutions`
  line `constituted under section 3;`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[(ca) "Competent authority" means the authority appointed by the appropriate Government to`
  line `grant no objection certificate for the establishment of any educational institution of their choice by the`
  line minorities;]
  line
  line `(d) "degree" means any such degree as may, with previous approval of the Central Government,`
  line `be specified in this behalf by the University Grants Commission, by notification in the Official`
  line Gazette;
  line
  line ^2
  line `[(da) "educational rights to minorities" means the rights of minorities to establish and administer`
  line `educational institutions of their choice;]`
  line
  line `(e) "Member" means a member of the Commission and includes the Chairperson;`
  line
  line `(f) "minority", for the purpose of this Act, means a community notified as such by the Central`
  line Government;
  line
  line ^4
  line `[(g) "Minority Educational Institution" means a college or an educational institution established`
  line `and administered by a minority or minorities;]`
  line
  line `(h) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(i) "qualification" means a degree or any other qualification awarded by a University;`
  line
  line ^5
  line `* * * * *`
  line
  line `(k) "technical education" has the meaning assigned to it in clause (g) of section 2 of the All India`
  line `Council for Technical Education Act, 1987 (52 of 1987);`
  line
  line `(l) "University" means a university defined under clause (f) of section 2 of the University Grants`
  line `Commission Act, 1956 (3 of 1956), and includes an institution deemed to be a University under`
  line `section 3 of that Act, or an institution specifically empowered by an Act of Parliament to confer or`
  line `grant degrees.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The word "Scheduled" omitted by Act 18 of 2006, s.2 (w.e.f. 23-1-2006).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 2, ibid. (w.e.f. 23-1-2006).`
  line
  line `3. Cl. (b) omitted by Act 20 of 2010, s. 2 (w.e.f.1-9-2010).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for cl. (g) (w.e.f. 1-9-2010).`
  line
  line `5. Cl. (j) omitted by Act 18 of 2006, s. 2 (w.e.f. 23-1-2006).`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (23477)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Constitution of National Commission for Minority Educational Institutions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 20 of 2010, s. 3, for "two members" (w.e.f. 1-9-2010).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00003_200502_1517807320310&sectionId=23477&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00003_200502_1517807320310
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central`
  line `Government shall, by notification in the Official Gazette, constitute a body to be known as the National`
  line `Commission for Minority Educational Institutions to exercise the powers conferred on, and to perform the`
  line `functions assigned to, it under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commission shall consist of a Chairperson and ^1`
  line `[three members] to be nominated by the`
  line `Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (23478)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Qualifications for appointment as Chairperson or other member.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00003_200502_1517807320310&sectionId=23478&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00003_200502_1517807320310
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) A person shall not be`
  line `qualified for appointment as the Chairperson unless he,--`
  line
  line `(a) is a member of a minority community; and`
  line
  line `(b) has been a Judge of a High Court.`
  line
  line `(2) A person shall not be qualified for appointment as a Member unless he,--`
  line
  line `(a) is a member of a minority community; and`
  line
  line `(b) is a person of eminence, ability and integrity.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (23479)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Term of office and conditions of service of Chairperson and Members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00003_200502_1517807320310&sectionId=23479&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00003_200502_1517807320310
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every Member`
  line `shall hold office for a term of five years from the date on which he assumes office.`
  line
  line `(2) A Member may, by writing under his hand addressed to the Central Government, resign from the`
  line `office of Chairperson or, as the case may be, of Member at any time.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government shall remove a person from the office of Member if that person--`
  line
  line `(a) becomes an undischarged insolvent;`
  line
  line `(b) is convicted and sentenced to imprisonment for an offence which, in the opinion of the`
  line `Central Government, involves moral turpitude;`
  line
  line `(c) becomes of unsound mind and stands so declared by a competent court;`
  line
  line `(d) refuses to act or becomes incapable of acting;`
  line
  line `(e) is, without obtaining leave of absence from the Commission, absent from three consecutive`
  line `meetings of the Commission; or`
  line
  line `(f) in the opinion of the Central Government, has so abused the position of Chairperson or`
  line `Member as to render that person's continuance in office detrimental to the public interest:`
  line
  line `Provided that no person shall be removed under this clause until that person has been given an`
  line `opportunity of being heard in the matter.`
  line
  line `(4) A vacancy caused under sub-section (2) or otherwise shall be filled by fresh nomination and a`
  line `person so nominated shall hold office for the unexpired period of the term for which his predecessor in`
  line `office would have held office if such vacancy had not arisen.`
  line
  line `(5) The salaries and allowances payable to, and the other terms and conditions of service of, the`
  line `Chairperson and Members shall be such as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (23480)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Officers and other employees of Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00003_200502_1517807320310&sectionId=23480&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00003_200502_1517807320310
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall provide the`
  line `Commission with a Secretary and such other officers and employees as may be necessary for the efficient`
  line `performance of the functions of the Commission under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The salaries and allowances payable to, and the other terms and conditions of service of, the`
  line `Secretary, officers and other employees appointed for the purpose of the Commission shall be such as`
  line `may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (23481)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Salaries and allowances to be paid out of grants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00003_200502_1517807320310&sectionId=23481&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00003_200502_1517807320310
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `The salaries and allowances payable to the`
  line `Chairperson and Members and the administrative expenses, including salaries, allowances and pensions`
  line `payable to the Secretary, officers and other employees referred to in section 6, shall be paid out of the`
  line `grants referred to in sub-section (1) of section 14.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (23482)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Vacancies, etc., not to invalidate proceedings of Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00003_200502_1517807320310&sectionId=23482&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00003_200502_1517807320310
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `No act or proceeding of the`
  line `commission shall be questioned or shall be invalid on the ground merely of the existence of any vacancy`
  line `or defect in the constitution of the Commission.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (23483)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Procedure to be regulated by Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00003_200502_1517807320310&sectionId=23483&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00003_200502_1517807320310
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commission shall meet as and when`
  line `necessary at such time and place as the Chairperson may think fit.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commission shall regulate its own procedure.`
  line
  line `(3) All orders and decisions of the Commission shall be authenticated by the Secretary or any other`
  line `officer of the Commission duly authorised by the Secretary in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (23484)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Right to establish a Minority Educational Institution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00003_200502_1517807320310&sectionId=23484&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00003_200502_1517807320310
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `^1[10. Right to establish a Minority Educational Institution.—^2`
  line `[(1) Subject to the provisions`
  line `contained in any other law for the time being in force, any person, who desires to establish a Minority`
  line `Educational Institution may apply to the competent authority for the grant of no objection certificate for`
  line `the said purpose.]`
  line
  line `(2) The Competent authority shall,--`
  line
  line `(a) on perusal of documents, affidavits or other evidence, if any; and`
  line
  line `(b) after giving an opportunity of being heard to the applicant,`
  line
  line `decide every application filed under sub-section (1) as expeditiously as possible and grant or reject the`
  line `application, as the case may be:`
  line
  line `Provided that where an application is rejected, the Competent authority shall communicate the same`
  line `to the applicant.`
  line
  line `(3) Where within a period of ninety days from the receipt of the application under sub-section (1) for`
  line `the grant of no objection certificate,--`
  line
  line `(a) the Competent authority does not grant such certificate; or`
  line
  line `(b) where an application has been rejected and the same has not been communicated to the person`
  line `who has applied for the grant of such certificate,`
  line
  line `it shall be deemed that the Competent authority has granted a no objection certificate to the applicant.`
  line
  line `(4) The applicant shall, on the grant of a no objection certificate or where the Competent authority has`
  line `deemed to have granted the no objection certificate, be entitled to commence and proceed with the`
  line `establishment of a Minority Educational Institution in accordance with the rules and regulations, as the`
  line `case may be, laid down by or under any law for the time being in force.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) "applicant" means any person who makes an application under sub-section (1) for`
  line `establishment of a Minority Educational Institution;`
  line
  line `(b) "no objection certificate" means a certificate stating therein, that the Competent authority has`
  line `no objection for the establishment of a Minority Educational Institution.]`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 2006, s.3, for CHAPTER III (w.e.f. 23-1-2006).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 20 of 2010, s. 4, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 1-9-2010).`
obj_root_law_sections_10_a:
  sectionId (23485)
  sectionNo 10A
  orderNo 11
  title `Right of a Minority Educational Institution to seek affiliation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_a_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 2006, s.3, for CHAPTER III (w.e.f. 23-1-2006).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00003_200502_1517807320310&sectionId=23485&sectionno=10A&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00003_200502_1517807320310
obj_root_law_sections_10_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[10A. Right of a Minority Educational Institution to seek affiliation.—(1) A Minority Educational`
  line `Institution may seek affiliation to any University of its choice subject to such affiliation being permissible`
  line `within the Act under which the said University is established.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person who is authorised in this behalf by the Minority Educational Institution, may file an`
  line `application for affiliation under sub-section (1) to a University in the manner prescribed by the Statute,`
  line `Ordinance, rules or regulations, of the University:`
  line
  line `Provided that such authorised person shall have right to know the status of such application after the`
  line `expiry of sixty days from the date of filing of such application.]`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (23486)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 12
  title `Functions of Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 2006, s.4, for cls. (b) and (c) (w.e.f. 23-1-2006).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00003_200502_1517807320310&sectionId=23486&sectionno=11&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00003_200502_1517807320310
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time`
  line `being in force, the Commission shall--`
  line
  line `(a) advise the Central Government or any State Government on any question relating to the`
  line `education of minorities that may be referred to it;`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(b) enquire, suo motu, or on a petition presented to it by any Minority Educational Institution, or`
  line `any person on its behalf into complaints regarding deprivation or violation of rights of minorities to`
  line `establish and administer educational institutions of their choice and any dispute relating to affiliation`
  line `to a University and report its finding to the appropriate Government for its implementation;`
  line
  line `(c) intervene in any proceeding involving any deprivation or violation of the educational rights of`
  line `the minorities before a court with the leave of such court;`
  line
  line `(d) review the safeguards provided by or under the Constitution, or any law for the time being in`
  line `force, for the protection of educational rights of the minorities and recommend measures for their`
  line `effective implementation;`
  line
  line `(e) specify measures to promote and preserve the minority status and character of institutions of`
  line `their choice established by minorities;`
  line
  line `(f) decide all questions relating to the status of any institution as a Minority Educational`
  line `Institution and declare its status as such;`
  line
  line `(g) make recommendations to the appropriate Government for the effective, implementation of`
  line `programmes and schemes relating to the Minority Educational Institutions; and`
  line
  line `(h) do such other acts and things as may be necessary, incidental or conducive to the attainment`
  line `of all or any of the objects of the Commission.]`
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (23487)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 13
  title `Powers of Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00003_200502_1517807320310&sectionId=23487&sectionno=12&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00003_200502_1517807320310
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any dispute arises between a minority educational institution and`
  line `a ^1`
  line `*** University relating to its affiliation to such University, the decision of the Commission thereon`
  line `shall be final.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commission shall, for the purposes of discharging its functions under this Act, have all the`
  line `powers of a civil court trying a suit and in particular, in respect of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) summoning and enforcing the attendance of any person from any part of India and examining`
  line `him on oath;`
  line
  line `(b) requiring the discovery and production of any document;`
  line
  line `(c) receiving evidence on affidavits;`
  line
  line `(d) subject to the provisions of sections 123 and 124 of the Indian Evidence Act, 1872 (1 of`
  line `1872), requisitioning any public record or document or copy of such record or document from any`
  line office;
  line
  line `(e) issuing commissions for the examination of witnesses or documents; and`
  line
  line `(f) any other matter which may be prescribed.`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[(3) Every proceeding before the Commission shall be deemed to be a judicial proceeding within the`
  line `meaning of sections 193 and 228, and for the purposes of section 196, of the Indian Penal Code (45 of`
  line `1860) and the Commission shall be deemed to be a civil court for the purposes of section 195 and Chapter`
  line `XXVI of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).]`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The word "Scheduled" omitted by s. 5, ibid. (w.e.f. 23-1-2006).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 18 of 2006, s. 5 (w.e.f. 23-1-2006).`
obj_root_law_sections_12_a:
  sectionId (23488)
  sectionNo 12A
  orderNo 14
  title `Appeal against orders of the Competent authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 6, ibid. (w.e.f. 23-1-2006).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00003_200502_1517807320310&sectionId=23488&sectionno=12A&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00003_200502_1517807320310
obj_root_law_sections_12_a_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[12A. Appeal against orders of the Competent authority.—(1) Any person aggrieved by the order`
  line `of refusal to grant no objection certificate under sub-section (2) of section 10 by the Competent authority`
  line `for establishing a Minority Educational Institution, may prefer an appeal against such order to the`
  line Commission.
  line
  line `(2) An appeal under sub-section (1) shall be filed within thirty days from the date of the order referred`
  line `to in sub-section (1) communicated to the applicant:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Commission may entertain an appeal after the expiry of the said period of thirty`
  line `days, if it is satisfied that there was sufficient cause for not filing it within that period.`
  line
  line `(3) An appeal to the Commission shall be made in such form as may be prescribed and shall be`
  line `accompanied by a copy of the order against which the appeal has been filed.`
  line
  line `(4) The Commission, after hearing the parties, shall pass an order as soon as may be practicable, and`
  line `give such directions as may be necessary or expedient to give effect to its orders or to prevent abuse of its`
  line `process or to secure the ends of justice.`
  line
  line `(5) An order made by the Commission under sub-section (4) shall be executable by the Commission`
  line `as a decree of a civil court and the provisions of the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), so far as`
  line `may be, shall apply as they apply in respect of a decree of a civil court.]`
obj_root_law_sections_12_b:
  sectionId (23489)
  sectionNo 12B
  orderNo 15
  title `Power of Commission to decide on the minority status of an educational institution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_b_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_b_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00003_200502_1517807320310&sectionId=23489&sectionno=12B&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00003_200502_1517807320310
obj_root_law_sections_12_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[12B. Power of Commission to decide on the minority status of an educational`
  line `institution.--(1) Without prejudice to the provisions contained in the National Commission for`
  line `Minorities Act, 1992 (19 of 1992), where an authority established by the Central Government or any State`
  line `Government, as the case may be, for grant of minority status to any educational institution rejects the`
  line `application for the grant of such status, the aggrieved person may appeal against such order of the`
  line `authority to the Commission.`
  line
  line `(2) An appeal under sub-section (1) shall be preferred within thirty days from the date of the order`
  line `communicated to the applicant:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Commission may entertain an appeal after the expiry of the said period of thirty`
  line `days, if it is satisfied that there was sufficient cause for not filing it within that period.`
  line
  line `(3) An appeal to the Commission shall be made in such form as may be prescribed and shall be`
  line `accompanied by a copy of the order against which the appeal has been filed.`
  line
  line `(4) On receipt of the appeal under sub-section (3), the Commission may, after giving the parties to the`
  line `appeal an opportunity of being heard, ^2`
  line `*** decide on the minority status of the educational institution and`
  line `shall proceed to give such direction as it may deem fit and, all such directions shall be binding on the`
  line parties.
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section and section 12C, "authority" means any authority or`
  line `officer or commission which is established under any law for the time being in force or under any order of`
  line `the appropriate Government, for the purpose of granting a certificate of minority status to an educational`
  line institution.]
obj_root_law_sections_12_b_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by s. 6, ibid. (w.e.f. 23-1-2006).`
  line
  line `2. The words "and in consultation with the State Government" omitted by Act 20 of 2010, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-9-2010).`
obj_root_law_sections_12_c:
  sectionId (23490)
  sectionNo 12C
  orderNo 16
  title `Power to cancel.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_c_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 6, ibid. (w.e.f. 23-1-2006).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00003_200502_1517807320310&sectionId=23490&sectionno=12C&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00003_200502_1517807320310
obj_root_law_sections_12_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[12C. Power to cancel.—The Commission may, after giving a reasonable opportunity of being heard`
  line `to a Minority Educational Institution to which minority status has been granted by an authority or Commission, as the case may be, cancel such status under the following circumstances, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) if the constitution, aims and objects of the educational institution, which has enabled it to`
  line `obtain minority status has subsequently been amended in such a way that it no longer reflects the`
  line `purpose or character of a Minority Educational Institution;`
  line
  line `(b) if, on verification of the records during the inspection or investigation, it is found that the`
  line `Minority Educational Institution has failed to admit students belonging to the minority community in`
  line `the institution as per rules and prescribed percentage governing admissions during any academic year.]`
obj_root_law_sections_12_d:
  sectionId (23491)
  sectionNo 12D
  orderNo 17
  title `Power of Commission to investigate matters relating to deprivation of educational rights of minorities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_d_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 6, ibid. (w.e.f. 23-1-2006).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00003_200502_1517807320310&sectionId=23491&sectionno=12D&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00003_200502_1517807320310
obj_root_law_sections_12_d_content:
  string
  line `^1[12D. Power of Commission to investigate matters relating to deprivation of educational rights`
  line `of minorities.—(1) The Commission shall have the power to investigate into the complaints relating to`
  line `deprivation of the educational rights of minorities.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commission may, for the purpose of conducting any investigation pertaining to a complaint`
  line `under this Act, utilise the services of any officer of the Central Government or any State Government with`
  line `the concurrence of the Central Government or the State Government, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(3) For the purpose of investigation under sub-section (1), the officer whose services are utilised may,`
  line `subject to the direction and control of the Commission,--`
  line
  line `(a) summon and enforce the attendance of any person and examine him;`
  line
  line `(b) require the discovery and production of any document; and`
  line
  line `(c) requisition any public record or copy thereof from any office.`
  line
  line `(4) The officer whose services are utilised under sub-section (2) shall investigate into any matter`
  line `entrusted to it by the Commission and submit a report thereon to it within such period as may be specified`
  line `by the Commission in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(5) The Commission shall satisfy itself about the correctness of the facts stated and the conclusion, if`
  line `any, arrived at in the report submitted to it under sub-section (4) and for this purpose the Commission`
  line `may make such further inquiry as it may think fit.]`
obj_root_law_sections_12_e:
  sectionId (23492)
  sectionNo 12E
  orderNo 18
  title `Power of Commission to call for information, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_e_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 6, ibid. (w.e.f. 23-1-2006).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00003_200502_1517807320310&sectionId=23492&sectionno=12E&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00003_200502_1517807320310
obj_root_law_sections_12_e_content:
  string
  line `^1[12E. Power of Commission to call for information, etc.--(1) The Commission, while enquiring`
  line `into the complaints of violation or deprivation of educational rights of minorities shall call for information`
  line `or report from the Central Government or any State Government or any other authority or organisation`
  line `subordinate thereto, within such time as may be specified by it:`
  line
  line `Provided that,--`
  line
  line `(a) if the information or report is not received within the time stipulated by the Commission, it`
  line `may proceed to inquire into the complaint;`
  line
  line `(b) if, on receipt of information or report, the Commission is satisfied either that no further`
  line `inquiry is required, or that the required action has been initiated or taken by the concerned`
  line `Government or authority, it may not proceed with the complaint and inform the complainant`
  line accordingly.
  line
  line `(2) Where the inquiry establishes violation or deprivation of the educational rights of the minorities`
  line `by a public servant, the Commission may recommend to the concerned Government or authority, the`
  line `initiation of disciplinary proceedings or such other action against the concerned person or persons as may`
  line `be deemed fit.`
  line
  line `(3) The Commission shall send a copy of the inquiry report, together with its recommendations to the`
  line `concerned Government or authority and the concerned Government authority shall, within a period of one`
  line `month, or such further time as the Commission may allow, forward its comments on the report, including`
  line `the action taken, or proposed to be taken thereon, to the Commission.`
  line
  line `(4) The Commission shall publish its inquiry report and the action taken or proposed to be taken by`
  line `the concerned Government or authority on the recommendations of the Commission.]`
obj_root_law_sections_12_f:
  sectionId (23493)
  sectionNo 12F
  orderNo 19
  title `Bar of jurisdiction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_f_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 6, ibid. (w.e.f. 23-1-2006).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00003_200502_1517807320310&sectionId=23493&sectionno=12F&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00003_200502_1517807320310
obj_root_law_sections_12_f_content:
  string
  line `^1[12F. Bar of jurisdiction.—No court (except the Supreme Court and a High Court exercising`
  line `jurisdiction under articles 226 and 227 of the Constitution) shall entertain any suit, application or other`
  line `proceedings in respect of any order made under this Chapter.]`
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (23494)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 20
  title `Financial and administrative powers of Chairperson.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00003_200502_1517807320310&sectionId=23494&sectionno=13&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00003_200502_1517807320310
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `The Chairperson shall exercise such`
  line `financial and administrative powers as may be vested in him by the rules made under this section:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Chairperson shall have authority to delegate such of the financial and administrative`
  line `powers as he may think fit to any Member or Secretary or any other officer of the Commission subject to`
  line `the condition that such Member or Secretary or officer shall, while exercising such delegated powers,`
  line `continue to act under the direction, control and supervision of the Chairperson.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (23495)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 21
  title `Grants by Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00003_200502_1517807320310&sectionId=23495&sectionno=14&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00003_200502_1517807320310
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall, after due appropriation`
  line `made by Parliament by law in this behalf, pay to the Commission by way of grants such sums of money`
  line `as the Central Government may think fit for being utilised for the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commission may spend such sums of money as it thinks fit for performing the functions`
  line `under this Act, and such sums shall be treated as expenditure payable out of the grants referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (23496)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 22
  title `Accounts and audit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00003_200502_1517807320310&sectionId=23496&sectionno=15&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00003_200502_1517807320310
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commission shall maintain proper accounts and other relevant`
  line `records and prepare an annual statement of accounts in such form as may be prescribed by the Central`
  line `Government in consultation with the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India.`
  line
  line `(2) The accounts of the Commission shall be audited by the Comptroller and Auditor-General at such`
  line `intervals as may be specified by him and any expenditure incurred in connection with such audit shall be`
  line `payable by the Commission to the Comptroller and Auditor-General.`
  line
  line `(3) The Comptroller and Auditor-General and any person appointed by him in connection with the`
  line `audit of the accounts of the Commission under this Act shall have the same rights and privileges and the`
  line `authority in connection with such audit as the Comptroller and Auditor-General generally has in`
  line `connection with the audit of Government accounts and, in particular, shall have the right to demand the`
  line `production of books, accounts, connected vouchers and other documents and papers and to inspect any of`
  line `the offices of the Commission.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (23497)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 23
  title `Annual report.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00003_200502_1517807320310&sectionId=23497&sectionno=16&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00003_200502_1517807320310
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `The Commission shall prepare, in such form and at such time, for each`
  line `financial year, as may be prescribed, its annual report, giving a full account of its activities during the`
  line `previous financial year and forward a copy thereof to the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (23498)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 24
  title `Annual report and audit report to be laid before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00003_200502_1517807320310&sectionId=23498&sectionno=17&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00003_200502_1517807320310
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government shall`
  line `cause the annual report, together with a memorandum of action taken on the advice tendered by the`
  line `Commission under section 11 and the reasons for the non-acceptance, if any, of any such advice, and the`
  line `audit report to be laid as soon as may be after they are received before each House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (23499)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 25
  title [Omitted.].
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00003_200502_1517807320310&sectionId=23499&sectionno=18&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00003_200502_1517807320310
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `[Power to amend Schedule.] Omitted by the National Commission for Minority Educational`
  line `Institutions (Amendment) Act, 2006 (18 of 2006), s. 7 (w.e.f. 23-1-2006).`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (23500)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 26
  title `Chairperson, Members, Secretary, employees, etc., of Commission to be public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00003_200502_1517807320310&sectionId=23500&sectionno=19&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00003_200502_1517807320310
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `The Chairperson, Members, Secretary, officers and other employees of the Commission shall`
  line `be deemed to be public servants within the meaning of section 21 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (23501)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 27
  title `Directions by Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00003_200502_1517807320310&sectionId=23501&sectionno=20&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00003_200502_1517807320310
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) In the discharge of its functions under this Act, the`
  line `Commission shall be guided by such direction on questions of policy relating to national purposes, as may`
  line `be given to it by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) If any dispute arises between the Central Government and the Commission as to whether a`
  line `question is or is not a question of policy relating to national purposes, the decision of the Central`
  line `Government shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (23502)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 28
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00003_200502_1517807320310&sectionId=23502&sectionno=21&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00003_200502_1517807320310
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall`
  line `lie against the Central Government, Commission, Chairperson, Members, Secretary or any officer or`
  line `other employee of the Commission for anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done under`
  line `this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (23503)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 29
  title `Act to have overriding effect.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00003_200502_1517807320310&sectionId=23503&sectionno=22&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00003_200502_1517807320310
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act shall have effect notwithstanding`
  line `anything inconsistent therewith contained in any other law for the time being in force or in any instrument`
  line `having effect by virtue of any law other than this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (23504)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 30
  title `Returns or information.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00003_200502_1517807320310&sectionId=23504&sectionno=23&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00003_200502_1517807320310
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `The Commission shall furnish to the Central Government such returns`
  line `or other information with respect to its activities as the Central Government may, from time to time,`
  line require.
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (23505)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 31
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 18 of 2006, s. 8 (w.e.f. 23-1-2006).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00003_200502_1517807320310&sectionId=23505&sectionno=24&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00003_200502_1517807320310
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules for carrying out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing powers, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the salaries and allowances payable to, and the other terms and conditions of the service of,`
  line `the Chairperson and Members under sub-section (5) of section 5 and of the Secretary, officers and`
  line `other employees under sub-section (2) of section 6;`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(aa) the forms in which appeal under sub-section (3) of the section 12A and sub-section (3) of`
  line `section 12B shall be made;]`
  line
  line `(b) the financial and administrative powers to be exercised by the Chairperson under section 13;`
  line
  line `(c) the form in which the annual statement of accounts shall be prepared under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 15;`
  line
  line `(d) the form in, and the time at, which the annual report shall be prepared under section 16;`
  line
  line `(e) any other matter which is required to be, or may be, prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each House`
  line `of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one`
  line `session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only`
  line `in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (23506)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 32
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00003_200502_1517807320310&sectionId=23506&sectionno=25&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00003_200502_1517807320310
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the Central Government may, by order published in the Official Gazette, make such provisions`
  line `not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, as appear to it to be necessary or expedient, for removing`
  line `the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made after the expiry of a period of two years from the date of`
  line `commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall, as soon as may be after it is made, be laid before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (23507)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 33
  title `Repeal and saving.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00003_200502_1517807320310&sectionId=23507&sectionno=26&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00003_200502_1517807320310
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) The National Commission for Minority Educational Institutions`
  line `Ordinance, 2004 (Ord. 6 of 2004) is hereby repealed.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding the repeal of the said Ordinance, anything done or any action taken under the`
  line `said Ordinance shall be deemed to have been done or taken under the corresponding provisions of this`
  line Act.
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
